# Quick Start

## Most Common Tasks

**When user asks to...**

| Task | Quick Action | Files to Check |
|------|-------------|----------------|
| Setup AWS credentials | Run `aws configure sso` (or project-specific profile) | See Authentication rules |
| Check TypeScript errors | Run `npm run type-check` or `npx tsc --noEmit` (before committing!) | All `.ts` and `.tsx` files |
| Fix authentication | Check SSO config | `amplify/auth/resource.ts`, `src/App.tsx` |
| Add new component | Extract to separate file if >300 lines | `src/components/` |
| Fix styling | Use only core Tailwind utilities | Any `.tsx` component file |
| Modify data model | Update schema + redeploy | `amplify/data/resource.ts` |
| Fix toast notifications | Use toast utilities, not alert() | `src/utils/toast.ts` |
| Debug ride/map issues | Check geoUtils, mapUtils, activeRideStorage | `src/utils/geoUtils.ts`, `src/utils/activeRideStorage.ts` |

## Quick Commands

```bash
# Development
npm run dev                    # Start dev server

# Amplify Backend (use project's AWS profile if configured)
npm run amplify:sandbox

# Code Quality (run before committing)
npm run type-check              # Check TypeScript errors
npm run lint                    # Run ESLint

# Testing
npm run test                    # Run Vitest unit tests
npm run test:e2e                # Run Playwright E2E tests

# Build & Deploy
npm run build                   # Build for production
npm run preview                 # Preview production build locally
```

**Note:** If the project uses a specific AWS profile for Amplify, add it to the `amplify:sandbox` script or pass `-- --profile YourProfile`.

